    <title type="text">Persian.ology [On the Persepolis Archives]</title>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<span style="font-family: inherit;"><span style="font-size:
      medium;"><a
      href="http://www.magcloud.com/guestpass/f70fff1ab2d4495a8147fa77ad438474?webviewer=False">Persian.ology:
      gate-keepers of (clay) dinosaur bones, the story of the discovery and recovery of the
      Persepolis (Parsa) administrative archives (Persepolis Fortification Archive and Persepolis
      Treasury Archive) in the early 1930s</a>. </span><span style="font-size:
      medium;">(114 pages, about 62M)</span></span><br /><span
      style="font-family: inherit;"><span style="font-size: medium;">By A. J. Cave, April
      2014</span></span><br /><blockquote class="tr_bq"><span
      style="font-family: inherit;"><span style="font-size: x-small;">persian.ology :
      gate-keepers of (clay) dinosaur bones is an informal look at the Persian Achaemenid
      Administrative Archives recovered from Pârsa (Persepolis), Iran, in
      1930s</span></span><br /><span style="font-family: inherit;"><span
      style="font-size: x-small;"><br />parts are taken from the
      books:</span></span><br /><span style="font-family: inherit;"><span
      style="font-size: medium;"><span style="font-size: x-small;"><br />an
      idol-worshiper’s Guide to god-stan: a Trilogy in 7 Parts (2012)<br />Cyrus 0.9:
      Highlander (2013)<br />“the Road to Persiana”, persian.ology Magazine
      (2013)</span></span></span></blockquote><br /><span
      style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: inherit;">Published in honor of
      the celebration of the lifelong achievements of Dr. Matthew <span class="mark"
      id="misspell-10">Stolper</span>, head of the <span class="mark"
      id="misspell-11">PFA</span> Project, Monday, 28 April 2014, at the Oriental
      Institute.</span></span><br /><br /><div class="MsoNormal"
      style="margin-bottom: 6pt; text-align: justify;"><span style="font-family:
      inherit;"><span style="font-size: small;">The smaller version (without couple of
      repeated sections on archives and administrative languages, about 11M) is posted <a
      href="https://www.academia.edu/6821524/Persian.ology_gate-keepers_of_clay_dinosaur_bones">here</a>,
      and <a
      href="https://www.dropbox.com/s/7jeivtsaaaecv7f/persianology-gatekeepers%20of%20clay%20dinosaur%20bones.pdf">here</a>.</span></span></div><span
      style="font-family: inherit;"><span style="font-size:
      medium;">&nbsp;</span></span> <br /><div style="text-align:
      center;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: inherit;">See
      Also:</span></span></div><div style="text-align: center;"><span
      style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: inherit;"><a class="GCUXF0KCPB"
      href="http://ancientworldonline.blogspot.com/2014/04/open-access-publications-on-persepolis.html">Open
      Access Publications on Persepolis from the Oriental
      Institute</a></span></span></div><br />]]></content>
